Uruk Axe x4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I have played this deck a few times with friends but have not taken it to a touney as of yet. I just might next time. It has yet to be beaten.<br />
<br />
Free Peoples Strategy-<br />
<br />
Fairly simple really. Take care of minions in a multitude of ways. Sent back, Down From The Hills on an invincible Gimli, Damage +1 Ents. The Down From the Hills are awesome with Gimli all decked out. Base strength 6, bracers, axe, hand axe, endurance, 3 exertions, Down From the Hills, dwarven armor makes Gimli unable to die unless the minions against him are strength 54. Since he can&#39;t take wounds, he takes on the 2 biggest minions if the need arises. Get out Treebeard and the Avengers and you are playing at least one Enraged every turn. With Sent back and the damage bonus ents, minions just don&#39;t hang around.<br />
<br />
Shadow Strategy - <br />
<br />
Get out Under the Watching Eyes as soon as you can. With your Uruk damage bonuses and Rank and File, this should spell doom for your opponent. The Uruk swarm capability is there because the Sauron Uruks are so cheap to play and Rank and File is ridiculously easy to load up with tokens.<br />
<br />
Any comments and suggestions are most welcome. Thanks! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
